ce:section.ce:para:
To investigate the practicability of MnO2 colorimetric nanoprobe, its UV–vis absorption optical properties was tested. In Fig. 2
                        , the MnO2 nano-oxidizer demonstrates a strong UV–vis absorption peak at 350 nm and shows bright yellow color in water. When glucose was added into the MnO2 nanoprobe, the UV–vis absorption peak gradually debased, demonstrating the successful reduction of MnO2 nano-oxidizer to Mn2+ along with the oxidation of glucose to gluconic acid (MnO2 + Glucose → Mn2+ + Gluconic acid). The corresponding photographs further attested the efficient redox reaction between MnO2 and glucose, in which the bright yellow MnO2 solution became to be colorless with the addition of glucose (Fig. 2). Moreover, the XPS measurements also identified this reaction mechanism. In the reaction solution of MnO2 and glucose, the characteristic Mn (2p, 3 s) peaks of Mn2+ were observed (Fig. 3
                        ), which was the same as that of MnO2 and GSH, further illustrating that the MnO2 nano-oxidizers bounded to be reduced to Mn2+ by the glucose (Fig. S2). Based on redox reaction, MnO2 nano-oxidizer can be further utilize to sense the other reducing sugars including maltose, galactose, fructose, etc. (Fig. S3). All the tests proved the feasibility of MnO2 nano-oxidizer for the colorimetric sensing of glucose.
